            <p class="text-justify">Summer break peeks a lot different this year than it did last year. With the approach of summer, the epidemic has entered a new stage. Many people in the United States have had all of their shots. Testing and quarantine regulations have become less stringent both domestically and internationally. The best place for Disease Control and Prevention keeps raised travel limitations for more than 100 destinations worldwide. Many travelers are taking advantage of their newfound freedom by reuniting with family and friends, revisiting old haunts, and finally scheduling those long-awaited travels. However, as many parts of the world remain in the grip of the pandemic, and regions across the United States tread cautiously toward a new normal, travel remains fraught with uncertainty from changing flight schedules to varying reopening timelines, and the numerous travel requirements and guidelines still in place. So here are some lists of U.S. travel news.</p>
            <h2 class="text-justify">Covid Cases, weather causes widespread flight cancellations: </h2>
            <p class="text-justify">Thousands of flights were canceled over the weekend and on Monday, as severe weather hit the United States and airlines coped with Covid-related personnel shortages. According to the flight tracking website, more than 1,300 flights out of or within the United States have canceled midday on January. If the flight is canceled, your airline will most likely rebook you on the next available flight to your destination, though, given the high number of cancellations, it may take some time for your trip to resume. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">If your journey begins outside the intended window for establishing your negative status due to a delay or cancellation, you may need to get retested for Covid. Check with your airline if you have any queries about whether you need to get retested before flying to the United States. For example, Delta states that you don't need to be retested if your first departure flight is delayed by 24 hours or less, and for connecting flights, the delay window is extended to 48 hours. </p>
